Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper proposes a novel framework for color constancy using deep learning-based models, which is a core area of computer vision. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The use of deep learning-based models and the incorporation of interpretability in the proposed framework falls under the scope of artificial intelligence. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper utilizes deep learning-based models and proposes a new building block, feature map reweight unit (ReWU), which is a machine learning technique. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The proposed framework can be applied to multimedia applications such as image and video processing. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The use of deep learning-based models in the proposed framework falls under the scope of neural computing.
